      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Joona Kiiski</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:202px;\"><a href=\"https://daylen.com/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/34/JoonaKiiski.jpg/200px-JoonaKiiski.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/3/34/JoonaKiiski.jpg 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:JoonaKiiski.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Daylen Yang <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div>\n<p><b>Joona Kiiski</b>,<br />\na Finnish software engineer with a Master's degree in physics from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_Jyv%C3%A4skyl%C3%A4\">University of Jyväskylä</a>, currently residing in <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/California\">California</a>, helping to pioneer in autonomous mobility <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Stockfish\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Stockfish</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Stockfish\">Stockfish</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Joona_Kiiski&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Stockfish\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>In 2009, Joona Kiiski tweaked <a href=\"/Tord_Romstad\" title=\"Tord Romstad\">Tord Romstad's</a> <a href=\"/Category:Open_Source\" title=\"Category:Open Source\">open source chess program</a> <a href=\"/Glaurung\" title=\"Glaurung\">Glaurung</a> and called it <a href=\"/Smaug\" title=\"Smaug\">Smaug</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> . The derivations of Glaurung, notably <a href=\"/Stockfish\" title=\"Stockfish\">Stockfish</a> by <a href=\"/Marco_Costalba\" title=\"Marco Costalba\">Marco Costalba</a> and <i>Smaug</i> was controversial, and other chess programmers were annoyed with their original efforts over years <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> , while Tord Romstad appreciated the development with his understanding and interpretation of the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_source\">open source</a> idea in competitive computer chess. In 2009 they joint forces on Stockfish, Marco's initial branch of Glaurung's evolutionary tree <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>.\n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Joona_Kiiski&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/Stockfish%27s_Tuning_Method\" title=\"Stockfish&#39;s Tuning Method\">Stockfish's Tuning Method</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Joona_Kiiski&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=26971\">Smaug: a new chess engine based on glaurung</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Joona Kiiski</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 12, 2009</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=40662\">Stockfish's tuning method</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Joona Kiiski</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 07, 2011&#160;» <a href=\"/Stockfish%27s_Tuning_Method\" title=\"Stockfish&#39;s Tuning Method\">Stockfish's Tuning Method</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=47953&amp;start=10\">Re: History pruning / move ordering question</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Joona Kiiski</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, May 12, 2013&#160;» <a href=\"/Countermove_Heuristic\" title=\"Countermove Heuristic\">Countermove Heuristic</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Joona_Kiiski&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/joona-kiiski-54425a31/\">Joona Kiiski | LinkedIn</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.stockfishchess.com/\">Stockfish Chess Engine Home</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.chessgames.com/perl/chessplayer?pid=64287\">The chess games of Joona Kiiski</a> from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.chessgames.com/index.html\">chessgames.com</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.schach-welt.de/schach/computerschach/interviews/romstad-kiiski-costalba-eng\">Computerschach, Interview with Tord Romstad (Norway), Joona Kiiski (Finland) and Marco Costalba (Italy)</a> by <a href=\"/Frank_Quisinsky\" title=\"Frank Quisinsky\">Frank Quisinsky</a>, March 29, 2010</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.chessdom.com/stockfish-4-to-play-in-the-new-season-of-tcec/\">Stockfish 4 to play in the new season of TCEC | Chessdom - Short interview with the Stockfish team</a>, August 22, 2013&#160;» <a href=\"/TCEC\" title=\"TCEC\">TCEC</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/zamar\">zamar · GitHub</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Joona Kiiski</a></li></ul>\n<dl><dd> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/zamar/spsa\">SPSA Tuner for Stockfish Chess Engine</a>   <sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></dd></dl>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/lantonov/Rockstar\">GitHub - lantonov/Rockstar: Implementation of ROCK* algorithm (Gaussian kernel regression + natural gradient descent) for optimisation</a> by <a href=\"/Lyudmil_Antonov\" title=\"Lyudmil Antonov\">Lyudmil Antonov</a> and <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Joona Kiiski</a>&#160;» <a href=\"/Automated_Tuning#Rockstar\" title=\"Automated Tuning\">Rockstar</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Joona_Kiiski&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/joona-kiiski-54425a31/\">Joona Kiiski | LinkedIn</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/joona-kiiski-54425a31/\">Joona Kiiski | LinkedIn</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=26971\">Smaug: a new chess engine based on glaurung</a> by Joona Kiiski, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 12, 2009</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=27758\">Trusted testers wanted</a> by <a href=\"/Volker_Annuss\" title=\"Volker Annuss\">Volker Annuss</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, May 05, 2009</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://wbec-ridderkerk.forumotion.com/wbec-ridderkerk-news-info-f1/stockfish-glaurung-t402.htm\">Stockfish - Glaurung</a> from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://wbec-ridderkerk.forumotion.com/forum.htm\">WBEC-Ridderkerk forum</a>, September, 2009</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=40662\">Stockfish's tuning method</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Joona Kiiski</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 07, 2011</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.jhuapl.edu/spsa/\">SPSA Algorithm</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<p><b><a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">Up one level</a></b>\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260301001016\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.017 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.019 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 121/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 266/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 0/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    0.000      1 -total\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key oscar70_mw1-mw_:pcache:idhash:3607-0!canonical and timestamp 20260301001016 and revision id 19680\n -->\n"
